Matter of Kenneth HUSNEY of Petition for Naturalization, Petitioner-Appellant, v. UNITED STATES of America, Respondent-Appellee. No. 317, Docket 24976. United States Court of Appeals Second Circuit. Argued May 15, 1958. Decided May 15, 1958. Abraham Ross, Laurelton, N. Y., for petitioner-appellant. Cornelius Wickersham, Jr., U. S. Atty., Eastern District of New York, Brooklyn, N. Y. (Robert A. Morse, Asst. U. S. Atty., Brooklyn, N. Y., on the brief), for respondent-appellee.

Before SWAN, HINCKS and LUMBARD, Circuit Judges.

PER CURIAM.

Affirmed in open court, 140 F.Supp. 503.
